@Rule:CitationContract @Role:Resident @Priority:High @fast
Feature: Memory recall behavior # features/memory_recall.feature:2
  In order to trust responses grounded in memory
  As a resident
  I want cited answers when memory is sufficient and progressive fallback when it is not
  Scenario: cited memory-grounded answer path                           # features/memory_recall.feature:7
    Given a deterministic in-memory recall harness                      # features/steps/memory_steps.py:232
    And eval cases are loaded from "eval/cases.jsonl"                   # features/steps/memory_steps.py:238
    When the user asks about eval case "sleep-followup"                 # features/steps/memory_steps.py:244
    Then the assistant returns a memory-grounded answer                 # features/steps/memory_steps.py:342
    And the answer includes citation fields "doc_id" and "ts"           # features/steps/memory_steps.py:349
    And the response includes memory provenance transparency fields     # features/steps/memory_steps.py:355
    And the response includes a grounding basis statement               # features/steps/memory_steps.py:363
    And the response includes deterministic citation-context formatting # features/steps/memory_steps.py:557

  Scenario: progressive assist fallback path                  # features/memory_recall.feature:17
    Given a deterministic in-memory recall harness            # features/steps/memory_steps.py:232
    And eval cases are loaded from "eval/cases.jsonl"         # features/steps/memory_steps.py:238
    When the user asks about eval case "no-memory-match"      # features/steps/memory_steps.py:244
    Then the assistant returns an assistive fallback response # features/steps/memory_steps.py:369

